The Chronicle Tonderai Zvimba, Showbiz Reporter RESTAURANT chain Pizza Hut Bulawayo, which is located at the Zonkizizwe shopping complex, is now offering a free delivery service within a 6km radius from Mondays to Thursdays. For one to get this free delivery, all they need to do is to buy a pizza worth US$9 and above. The restaurant’s spokesperson Simbisai Nyamupachitu said they are running this promotion in order to deliver their pizzas fast and hot to their customers. “Whenever our customers order a pizza between Mondays and Thursdays, we deliver it to them for free. We’re doing this so as to serve them our restaurant’s quality pan pizza while its hot,” said Nyamupachitu.